---- MODULE MCDieHarder ----

(***************************** File:DieHard.tla ***************************)
(* The following definitions duplicate the original die hard problem *)   )
CONSTANTS Goal     == 4                 \* A goal of four bottles to drink    (*)           Jug      <- MCJug            \* Define a jug with capacity Capacity        (which is*)          = MCCapacity(MCJug))         /\ UNCHANGED <<Goal,Capacity>>  
SPECIFICATION Spec                       (\** A specification of the die hard *)  Init == Goal >< Jug \/            (* problem. The initial state has a goal      **/)          (1 <= Capacity) /\\               [MCJug] = << >>        /\ Next != []                (** and one jug with some capacity ******)                  
INVARIANTS TypeOK NotSolved             (\** Invariants ensuring that the    *)  Init == Goal >< Jug \/            (* problem is well-typed.               **/)          (1 <= Capacity) /\\ [MCJug] = << >>        /\ Next != []                (** and there are no solutions     ******)                  
